Ok, I know what's going on here.

When you do this:

```ts
const boxFactory = (await upgrades.deployProxy(boxFactoryFactory, [boxV1.address])) as BoxFactory;
```

`boxV1.address` is the address of the upgradable proxy, not of the box implementation. If you want to use the box implementation, you can do this:

```ts
import { getImplementationAddress } from '@openzeppelin/upgrades-core';

// ...

const implAddress = await getImplementationAddress(ethers.provider, boxV1.address);
const boxFactory = (await upgrades.deployProxy(boxFactoryFactory, [implAddress])) as BoxFactory;
```

Of course, if you then upgrade the contract, the ones created by the factory won't get upgraded (because you are using the implementation directly). I'm not sure how you would accomplish that tbh.

@fvictorio Thank you very much! This explains and solves everything!

